%T A394518 389221827287,392517991487,418189826521,442232779217,541031900449,
%U A394518 565496364383,566466791243,571344103879,645163729201,667207953649,671724886997,673415615521,679136613949,679833144947,685049373923
%N A394518 Sierpiński numbers that have at least three covering sets.
%C A394518 Numbers k such that k*2^n+1 is composite for all n>=1, and for which there exist at least three distinct finite sets of primes (covering sets) that prove this property.
%H A394518 Emilia Gurisatti, <a href="/A394518/b394518.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..27</a>
%H A394518 Emilia Gurisatti, <a href="https://github.com/emiguri/A394518/blob/main/b394518.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n=1..27 with its three covering sets</a>
%H A394518 W. Sierpiński, <a href="https://www.e-periodica.ch/cntmng?pid=edm-001%3A1960%3A15%3A%3A132">Sur un problème concernant les nombres k * 2^n + 1</a>, Elem. Math., 15 (1960), pp. 73-74.
%e A394518 For every k >= 1, 56889499253*2^k + 1 has a divisor in the set {3,5,7,13,17,241}, in the set {3,5,7,13,37,73,109} and also in the set {3,5,7,13,19,37,109}. 56889499253 is therefore in the sequence.
%Y A394518 Cf. A076336, A394519, A263391, A263392.
%K A394518 nonn
%O A394518 1,1
